cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.CL 

This paper deals with the problem of one-shot segmentation, which is a subfield of computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a novel dataset and uses machine learning models, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the use of attention mechanisms and iterative refinement, which could place it in the sub-categories of cs.RO (Robotics) and cs.CL (Computation and Language).
